These animals sighted at distance but were close to boat as we began station CTD operations.  2 humpback whales, circling ship within 20 feet while on station 87/50.  Trumpeting, surfacing towards vessel, looking back at ship.  Most activity positioned starboard side, by CTD platform.  Larger of 2 animals had 3/4 white pec fins, all black fluke.  Smaller whale had 3/4 white fluke.  Humpbacks around the ship for 1 hour 40 mins, ranging within 20-200 meters of the ship.  Line 87, station 55.
